==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: jean
<hw>jean</hw> <pr>(j⟦amac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. named from
<ets>Genoa</ets>. See <er>Jane</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A twilled
cotton cloth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>(pl.)</pluf> <pr>(j⟦emac⟧nz)</pr>, <def>Same as
<er>blue jeans</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <pluf>(pl.)</pluf> <pr>(j⟦emac⟧nz)</pr>, <def>Pants made
of different fabrics, resembling <er>blue jeans</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Satin jean</b></col>, <cd>a kind of jean woven smooth and
glossy, after the manner of satin.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jears</ent>⟦br⟧
